# App Header Standard

Every screen and modal in the app uses **one consistent header pattern** via `AppHeader`. Never implement inline headers.

## Layout (always the same)

```
[ < chevron ]     Title (centered)     [ action or empty ]
```

- **Left:** chevron-left icon — always dismisses or navigates back
- **Center:** title, always centered; optional subtitle below
- **Right:** optional action — text label ("Save", "Done") or icon ("+", trash), or empty

## Usage

```tsx
import AppHeader from '@/components/AppHeader';

// Minimal — back defaults to router.back()
<AppHeader title="Define Your Identity" showBorder={false} />

// With a right icon action
<AppHeader title="My Habits" rightAction={{ icon: 'plus', onPress: handleAdd }} />

// Inside a Modal — pass onBack to dismiss
<AppHeader title="Goal Detail" onBack={onClose} />

// With a right text action (Save / Done)
<AppHeader
  title="Edit Metrics"
  onBack={handleCancel}
  rightAction={{ label: 'Done', onPress: handleSave }}
/>

// Disabled right action
<AppHeader
  title="Daily Journal"
  onBack={handleClose}
  rightAction={{ label: 'Save', onPress: handleSubmit, disabled: !canSave }}
/>

// With subtitle
<AppHeader title="Weekly Recap" subtitle="Mar 3 – Mar 9" onBack={handleClose} />

// With a colored icon action
<AppHeader
  title={goal.title}
  onBack={onClose}
  rightAction={{ icon: 'trash-o', onPress: handleDelete, color: colors.danger }}
/>
```

## Props

- `title` (string, required) — centered title text
- `subtitle` (string) — smaller text below the title
- `onBack` (() => void) — left chevron handler; defaults to `router.back()`
- `rightAction` ({ icon?, label?, onPress, disabled?, color? }) — optional right slot
- `showBorder` (boolean, default false) — bottom border; leave off unless a specific screen needs it

## Common mistakes

- Writing a custom header View with inline styles instead of using `AppHeader`
- Using an X icon, "Close" text, or "Cancel" text to dismiss — always use the chevron via `onBack`
- Forgetting to pass `onBack` inside a React Native `Modal` (it won't default correctly to `router.back()`)
- Adding `showBorder={true}` without a clear reason — the default is borderless for a clean, modern look
